Through the row delimeter project, we had a system to generate different rows from a screenshot of a data set. IE given the information from that project, we can ask Chat
GPT to take a screenshot of our table, and it will find the rows and return cropped versions. This method worked fairly well for the 2 columns table. (see the cropped row images
png files)
My next goal was to get chat to generate code that can read these cropped images and return the numbers seen. Sadly chat used "built-in visual recognition capabilities to directly
interpret the numbers from the image you uploaded." IE it did not use code. 
When I asked it to generate an equivalent python script, the script did not work, even after multiple adjustments. (see NumberDection.py in the the row_delimeter_detection repo)
However with more prompting, this method has the potential to work.

My other focus was to achieve a similar results by building my own GPT. This is a easy process that OpenAI has its own UI for. It essentially interprets my request 
as instructions for the output of a chat text. However this method was also not promising. 
